<section id="slr_equivStorage">
  <title>slr_equivStorage</title>

  <para>This <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>string property
    <?oxy_custom_end?>provides a means to specify how much storage space an inline element will use
    in the native format. This size contribution is then added to the size contributed by the
    textual parts. This <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>string
    property <?oxy_custom_end?>is only allowed on the <olink
      targetdoc="../../elements/inline/ec.xml" targetptr="ec"><code>ec</code></olink> element if
    that element has the <olink targetdoc="../isolated.xml" targetptr="isolated"
        ><code>isolated</code></olink>
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>property<?oxy_custom_end?>
    set to <code>"yes"</code>. Otherwise the property on the paired <olink
      targetdoc="../../elements/inline/sc.xml" targetptr="sc"><code>sc</code></olink> element also
    cover its partner <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/ec.xml" targetptr="ec"
      ><code>ec</code></olink> element.</para>

  <para><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="140,255,140"?><emphasis>Type:</emphasis>
    string.<?oxy_custom_end?></para>
  <para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis> Interpretation of the value is dependent on selected
      <olink targetdoc="storage-profile.xml" targetptr="slr_storage_profile"
        ><code>slr_storageProfile</code></olink>. It <glossterm>must</glossterm> represent the
    equivalent storage size represented by the inline element.</para>

  <para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis> undefined.</para>

  <para><emphasis>Used
      in:<?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,64,0"?></emphasis>
    <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/pc.xml" targetptr="pc"><code>&lt;pc></code></olink>,
      <?oxy_custom_end?><olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/sc.xml" targetptr="sc"
        ><code>sc</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/ec.xml" targetptr="ec"
        ><code>ec</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/ph.xml" targetptr="ph"
        ><code>ph</code></olink>.</para>
</section>
